Workshop Goals
This workshop is not exhaustive but meant to be a first contact with the R programming language. We hope you leave the workshop able to say:

R isnâ€™t scary!

We also hope to show you you can use R to do things with data youâ€™re already familiar with, as well as clinical computations.
Object Types
Data Frames in R are like Datasets in SASÂ®. Data frames are made up of columns called vectors â€“ treated like Variables in SASÂ® More data types exist, but weâ€™ll focus on data frames

Basic Variable Types
Numeric
Character
Boolean


